<!-- Awards No limit --> | award1Pub = [[Independent Games Festival|IGF China]] | award1 = Excellence in Design<ref name="igfchina"/> | award2Pub = [[Indiecade]] | award2 = Excellence in Visual Design<ref name="indiecade"/> | award3Pub = [[Independent Games Festival|IGF]] | award3 = Finalist - Excellence in Design<ref name="igf"/> | award4Pub = [[Kotaku]] | award4 = 2014 Best Australian Game<ref name="kotakubestaus"/> | award5Pub = [[Kotaku]] | award5 = 2014 Best Mobile Game<ref name="kotakubestmobile"/> | award6Pub = [[Freeplay Independent Games Festival|Freeplay]] | award6 = 2013 Best Game<ref name="freeplaybest"/> | award7Pub = [[Freeplay Independent Games Festival|Freeplay]] | award7 = 2013 Best Design<ref name="freeplaybest"/> | award8Pub = [[International Mobile Game Awards|IMGAwards]] | award8 = 2014 Best Upcoming Game<ref name="imga"/> | award9Pub = [[Brazil Independent Game Festival|BIG Festival]] | award9 = 2014 Best Narrative <ref name="big"/> | award10Pub = [[Intel Level Up Awards|Intel Level Up]] | award10 = 2014 Best Puzzle Game <ref name="intel"/> | award11Pub = [[PAX Prime]] | award11 = PAX 10 2014 <ref name="pax10"/> | award12Pub = [[Tokyo Game Show]] | award12 = Sense of Wonder Night 2013 <ref name="sown"/> }} As of July 2015, ''Framed'' has received over 30 awards and accolades.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://framed-game.com/presskit/sheet.php?p=framed#awards|title=Loveshack Presskit - Framed|work=framed-game.com|accessdate=6 August 2015}}</ref> It has been praised by critics for its "brilliantly simple idea", "pitch perfect" execution, "subtle story telling", "gorgeous visuals", and "finger-snapping music".<ref name="pocketgamer"/><ref name="smh"/><ref name="kotakubestaus"/>
In November 2014, [[Hideo Kojima]], creator of the [[Metal Gear]] series stated that ''Framed'' was his [[Game of the Year]]. He praised ''Framed'' for its "high sense of gameplay, graphic, & sound", adding, "my best game in this year without any doubt".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/hideo-kojima-s-favorite-game-of-2014/1100-6423792/|title=Hideo Kojima's Favorite Game of 2014|work=GameSpot|accessdate=6 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kotaku.com.au/2014/11/hideo-kojimas-game-of-the-year-was-made-in-melbourne/|title=Hideo Kojima's Game Of The Year Was Made In Melbourne|author=Mark Serrels|work=kotaku.com.au|accessdate=6 August 2015}}</ref>
