[[File:Gerard Cox portret.jpg|thumb|150px|Gerard Cox]]
'''Gerardus Antonius "Gerard" Cox''' (born 6 March 1940, [[Rotterdam]]) is a Dutch singer, cabaret artist and actor. For fifteen years, he played the lead character of the Dutch sitcom ''[[Toen Was Geluk Heel Gewoon]]''. In 2018, Cox had a leading role in the RTL 4 alternative comedy series ''[[Grandpas Over Flowers|Beter Laat Dan Nooit]]'', where he travels around the world with other Dutch celebrities, which include [[Peter Faber (actor)|Peter Faber]], [[Willibrord Frequin]] and [[Barrie Stevens]].
