{{Infobox singer | name = Tuesday Vargas | image = File:Tuesday_Vargas_2013-10-26_12-25.jpg | caption = Vargas on 2013 | birth_name = Marizel Sarangelo | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1980|11|9}} | birth_place = [[Sampaloc, Manila]], Philippines | death_date = | death_place = | other_names = | occupation = {{Flatlist| *Actress *comedian *event organizer *host *band vocalist }} | years_active = 1996–present | agent = | known_for = | notable_works = | background = solo_singer | genre = {{Flatlist| *[[Pinoy pop]] *[[Original Pilipino Music|OPM]] }} | instrument = {{Flatlist| *Vocals *guitar *ukelele }} | associated_acts = {{Flatlist| *[[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]] *[[GMA Network]] *[[The 5 Network]] *[[Top Junk]] }} }} '''Marizel Sarangelo Placido''' (born November 9, 1980) better known her [[stage name]] as '''Tuesday Vargas''', is a [[Filipino people|Filipina]] [[singer]], [[actress]], [[comedian]] and a resident judge of [[TV5 (Philippines)|TV5's]] ''[[Talentadong Pinoy]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/231621/tv5-breaks-boundaries-announces-good-news-2010 |title=TV5 breaks boundaries; announces good news for 2010 |first=Jecelyn |last=Macahindog |work=[[Manila Bulletin]] |date=2009-11-28 |accessdate=2011-07-16}}</ref>
==Personal life== Born as '''Marizel Sarangelo''' on October 14, 1979 in Sampaloc, Manila. She is an alumna of [[Manila Science High School]].
==Career== Vargas is also known for her TV host and acting work outside of her comedian genre programs she had starred in 2006 on both ''[[Gulong ng Palad]]'' as Saling and ''[[Bituing Walang Ningning]]'' as Libby. She starred on [[Hiram na Mukha (TV series)|Hiram na Mukha]] in 2007 and also in 2008 [[Kaputol ng Isang Awit]]. In 2010 Tuesday gained recognition in the film Here Comes The Bride and 2012 independent fil Ang Turkey Man Ay Pabo Rin which had a spin off TV series in 2015 by Unitel Films Television Distribution that aired on TV 5.
